Wash and dry produce.

Zest and quarter @lemon{1}; trim and quarter @zucchini{1} lengthwise; cut crosswise into
1⁄2-inch-thick quarter-moons. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). 
Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}.

== Rice ==

In a #small pot{}, combine @basmati rice{1/2%cup}, 3⁄4 cup water (1 1⁄2 cups for 4 servings),
and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer.

Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Lemon Crema ==

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{3%tablespoon}, a squeeze of lemon juice
(big squeeze for 4 servings), a pinch of @salt{pinch}, and as much lemon zest as you like.

Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Taste and season
with @salt{} and @pepper{} if desired.

== Tagine ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
zucchini; cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Transfer to a #plate{}; wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for zucchini over medium-high heat. Add
@ground turkey{10%ounce}, onion, and @Tunisian spice blend{1%tablespoon}; season with
salt and pepper. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through,
~{4-6%minutes}.

Add garlic and zucchini; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Stir in @chickpeas{1%unit} and their liquid and @chicken stock concentrate{3%unit}; cook
until liquid has reduced by half, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

Remove from heat and stir in a squeeze of lemon juice (big squeeze for 4 servings).
Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}.

Divide rice between plates. Top with tagine and drizzle with lemon crema. Serve with
remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Ground Turkey is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.